Calculate species sensitivity from traits

Compiled on Sun Aug 23 11:55:04 2020 by ohara

knitr::opts_chunk$set(fig.width = 6, fig.height = 4, fig.path = 'figs/',
                      echo = TRUE, message = FALSE, warning = FALSE)

source('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oharac/src/master/R/common.R')

1 Summary

Read in Excel spreadsheets of taxonomic traits filled in by taxon experts. Process into a long/tidy format with checks on validity of category values. Identify categories that were assigned non-valid values.

2 Data

_raw_data/all_taxa_trait_data.xlsx is the raw workbook prepared by Nathalie Butt from the various submissions of the taxa-group experts. This has been processed and cleaned to _data/spp_traits_valid.csv.

excel_files/trait_stressor_sens_tidy.xlsx is a workbook with each sheet indicating a stressor, and sensitivity scores for each trait with respect to that stressor.

3 Methods

3.1 Use scored sensitivity traits to stressors against species scored to traits

Set up a function to consistently clean trait values. Trait values in the species trait file are already cleaned and adjusted in many cases to get around mismatches; they are generally lower case, no punctuation except for greater/less than signs.

This function also cleans up category and trait names for consistency. All lower case, punctuation and spaces replaced with underscores. Again, the species trait file is already cleaned in this manner.

clean_traits <- function(df, overwrite_clean_col = FALSE) {
  df <- df %>% 
    mutate(category = str_replace_all(category, '[^A-Za-z0-9]+', '_') %>% tolower(),
           category = str_replace_all(category, '^_|_$', ''),
           trait    = str_replace_all(trait, '[^A-Za-z0-9]+', '_') %>% tolower(),
           trait    = str_replace_all(trait, '^_|_$', ''))
  if(!overwrite_clean_col & ('trait_val_clean' %in% names(df))) {
      return(df) ### without overwriting existing trait_val_clean
  }
  if(overwrite_clean_col & ('trait_val_clean' %in% names(df))) {
    x <- readline(prompt = 'Overwriting existing trait_val_clean column? y/n ')
    if(str_detect(x, '^n')) stop('dammit!')
  }
  ### overwrite existing, or add new
  df <- df %>%
    mutate(trait_val_clean = str_replace_all(tolower(trait_value), '[^0-9a-z<>]', ''))
  
  return(df)
}

Since the species trait file is already cleaned, DO NOT use the clean_traits function - it will overwrite the trait_val_clean column.

spp_traits <- read_csv('_data/spp_traits_valid.csv') %>%
  mutate(spp_gp = str_replace_all(spp_gp, '\\(|\\)', ''),
         spp_gp = str_replace_all(spp_gp, '\\n', ' '))
str_sens_traits_file <- here('trait_stressor_rankings/trait_stressor_sens.xlsx')
layers <- readxl::excel_sheets(str_sens_traits_file)
str_sens_trait_scores <- lapply(layers,
        FUN = function(l) { # l <- layers[1]
          df <- readxl::read_excel(str_sens_traits_file, sheet = l) %>%
            mutate(stressor = l)
          if(class(df$sens_score) == 'character') {
            df <- df %>% 
              mutate(sens_score = case_when(
                str_detect(tolower(sens_score), '^y') ~ 1,
                str_detect(tolower(sens_score), '^n') ~ 0,
                TRUE ~  as.numeric(sens_score)))
          }
          return(df)
        }) %>%
  bind_rows() %>%
  clean_traits() %>%
  ### drop these - going into other categories - we'll change the sheets later
  filter(!str_detect(category, 'spatial_scale|breeding_nesting|foraging_range'))

spp_sens <- spp_traits %>%
  left_join(str_sens_trait_scores, by = c('category', 'trait', 'trait_val_clean')) %>%
  filter(!is.na(stressor)) %>%
  group_by(spp_gp, stressor, sheet) %>%
  summarize(sens_score = sum(sens_score, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  ungroup()
y <- str_sens_trait_scores %>%
  filter(stressor == 'wildlife_strike') %>%
  select(category, trait, trait_value, s = sens_score) %>%
  group_by(category, trait) %>%
  filter(any(s > 0)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  distinct()

vaq_df <- spp_traits %>%
  filter(str_detect(tolower(spp_gp), '^vaquita')) %>%
  right_join(y, by = c('category', 'trait', 'trait_value')) %>%

  mutate(spp_trait = ifelse(is.na(spp_gp), 0, 1)) %>%

combo_df <- y %>%
  select(-category) %>%
  mutate(a = auk_df$a,
         v = vaq_df$v)

3.2 Score general adaptive capacity

General adaptive capacity traits are basically related to the overall populations resilience in the face of a threat. Large extents of occurrence, large population sizes, presence of multiple subpopulations, and reproductive strategies fall into this category.

adcap_gen_traits_file <- here('trait_stressor_rankings/trait_stressor_adcap_general.xlsx')

adcap_gen_traits <- readxl::read_excel(adcap_gen_traits_file) %>%
  # filter(trait != 'max age' & trait != 'if one/few, size') %>%
  mutate(adcap_score = as.numeric(adcap_score)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(adcap_score)) %>%
  clean_traits()

spp_adcap_gen <- spp_traits %>%
  select(-trait_value) %>%
  left_join(adcap_gen_traits, by = c('category', 'trait', 'trait_val_clean')) %>%
  group_by(spp_gp, sheet) %>%
  summarize(adcap_gen_score = sum(adcap_score, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  ungroup()
  
# hist(spp_adcap_gen$adcap_gen_score)
p <- ggplot(spp_adcap_gen, aes(x = sheet, y = adcap_gen_score)) +
  geom_jitter(size = 1, alpha = .6, width = .2) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = .5))

ggsave(here('figs/spp_adcap_gen_scores.png'), height = 6, width = 6, dpi = 300)

3.3 Score specific adaptive capacity

Specific adaptive capacity traits are basically related to an organisms ability to avoid or mitigate exposure, primarily through movement and larval dispersal.

adcap_spec_traits_file <- here('trait_stressor_rankings/trait_stressor_adcap_specific.xlsx')

layers <- readxl::excel_sheets(adcap_spec_traits_file)
adcap_spec_traits <- lapply(layers,
        FUN = function(l) { # l <- layers[1]
          df <- readxl::read_excel(adcap_spec_traits_file, sheet = l) %>%
            mutate(stressor = l)
          if(class(df$adcap_score) == 'character') {
            df <- df %>% 
              mutate(adcap_score = case_when(
                str_detect(tolower(adcap_score), '^y') ~ 1,
                str_detect(tolower(adcap_score), '^n') ~ 0,
                TRUE ~  as.numeric(adcap_score)))
          }
          return(df)
        }) %>%
  bind_rows() %>%
  clean_traits() %>%
  filter(!str_detect(category, 'spatial_scale'))

spp_adcap_spec <- spp_traits %>%
  select(-trait_value) %>%
  left_join(adcap_spec_traits, by = c('category', 'trait', 'trait_val_clean')) %>%
  filter(!is.na(stressor)) %>%
  group_by(spp_gp, stressor, sheet) %>%
  summarize(adcap_spec_score = sum(adcap_score, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  ungroup()

3.4 Assign exposure potential modifier

Exposure potential modifier checks whether the depth and oceanic zones of the stressor match with the depth and oceanic zones of the species. These fall into the spatial scale category with the exception of EOO.

str_exposure_file <- here('trait_stressor_rankings/trait_stressor_adcap_specific.xlsx')

layers <- readxl::excel_sheets(str_exposure_file)
str_exposure <- lapply(layers,
        FUN = function(l) { # l <- layers[1]
          df <- readxl::read_excel(str_exposure_file, sheet = l) %>%
            mutate(stressor = l)
          if(class(df$adcap_score) == 'character') {
            df <- df %>% 
              mutate(adcap_score = case_when(
                str_detect(tolower(adcap_score), '^y') ~ 1,
                str_detect(tolower(adcap_score), '^n') ~ 0,
                TRUE ~ as.numeric(adcap_score)))
          }
          return(df)
        }) %>%
  bind_rows() %>%
  clean_traits() %>%
  rename(exposure = adcap_score) %>%
  filter(str_detect(category, 'spatial_scale'))

spp_exposure <- spp_traits %>%
  select(-trait_value) %>%
  left_join(str_exposure, by = c('category', 'trait', 'trait_val_clean')) %>%
  filter(!is.na(stressor)) %>%
  group_by(spp_gp, stressor, sheet) %>%
  summarize(exposure_mod = as.integer(sum(exposure, na.rm = TRUE) > 0)) %>%
  ungroup()  %>%
  arrange(stressor, sheet)
  
non_exposures <- spp_exposure %>% 
  filter(exposure_mod == 0) %>% 
  group_by(sheet, stressor) %>% 
  summarize(n_spp_gps = n_distinct(spp_gp)) %>%
  arrange(stressor, desc(n_spp_gps))

4 Combine scores

We will try a calculation for vulnerability \(V\) of species \(i\) to stressor \(j\) that basically looks like this:

\[\text{sensitivity score } S_{i,j} = \mathbf{s}_j^T \mathbf{t}_i\] based on a vector \(\mathbf{s}_j\) of trait-based sensitivity to stressor \(j\), and vector \(\mathbf{t}_i\) of traits of species \(i\);

\[\text{specific adaptive capacity score } K_{i,j} = \mathbf{k}_j^T \mathbf{t}_i\] based on vector \(\mathbf{k}_j\) of trait-based specific adaptive capacity to stressor \(j\); \[\text{general adaptive capacity score } G_{i} = \mathbf{g}^T \mathbf{t}_i\] based on vector \(\mathbf{g}\) of trait-based general adaptive capacity;

\[\text{exposure potential modifier } E_{i,j} = \begin{cases} 1 \text{ when }\mathbf{e}_j^T \mathbf{t}_i > 0\\ 0 \text{ else} \end{cases}\] based on vector \(\mathbf{e}_j\) of trait-based presence of stressor \(j\) (i.e.depth zones and ocean zones in which stressor occurs).

\[\text{vulnerability } V_{i,j} = \frac{S_{i,j} / \bar{S_j}}{1 + G_i/\bar{G} + K_{i,j}/\bar{K_j}} \times E_{i,j}\] Each component (\(S_{i,j}, G_i, K_{i,j}\)) is normalized by the mean value for that component for that stressor across all species.

For species with NA in specific adaptive capacity, force to zero (no matching adaptive traits); for species with NA in exposure potential, force to 1 (assume exposure potential).

spp_vulnerability <- spp_sens %>%
  left_join(spp_adcap_gen, by = c('sheet', 'spp_gp')) %>%
  left_join(spp_adcap_spec, by = c('sheet', 'spp_gp', 'stressor')) %>%
  left_join(spp_exposure, by = c('sheet', 'spp_gp', 'stressor')) %>%
  ### fix NAs
  mutate(adcap_spec_score = ifelse(is.na(adcap_spec_score), 0, adcap_spec_score),
         exposure_mod     = ifelse(is.na(exposure_mod), 1, exposure_mod)) %>%
  ### calculate means.  General adcap is overall; specific adcap and sensitivity are by stressor
  group_by(stressor) %>%
  mutate(mean_adcap_spec = mean(adcap_spec_score),
         mean_sens = mean(sens_score)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(mean_adcap_gen = mean(adcap_gen_score)) %>%
  ### rescale components
  mutate(sens_rescale = sens_score / mean_sens,
         adcap_gen_rescale = adcap_gen_score / mean_adcap_gen,
         adcap_spec_rescale = adcap_spec_score / mean_adcap_spec) %>%
  ### mash 'em all together
  mutate(vuln = sens_rescale / (1 + adcap_gen_rescale + adcap_spec_rescale) * exposure_mod)

vuln_plot <- ggplot(spp_vulnerability, aes(x = stressor, y = vuln)) +
  ggtheme_plot(base_size = 7) +
  geom_jitter(size = 1, alpha = .6, width = .2, height = .05) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = .5),
        strip.background = element_rect(fill = 'grey90')) +
  facet_wrap(~ sheet, scales = 'free_y')

ggsave(plot = vuln_plot, filename = here('figs/vuln_plot.png'), width = 6, height = 5, dpi = 300)
knitr::include_graphics(here('figs/vuln_plot.png'))

4.1 examine components by taxon and stressor

spp_vuln_summary <- spp_vulnerability %>%
  group_by(sheet, stressor) %>%
  summarize(n_spp = n_distinct(spp_gp),
            sens_mean = mean(sens_rescale),
            sens_sd   = sd(sens_rescale),
            gen_mean  = mean(adcap_gen_rescale),
            gen_sd    = sd(adcap_gen_rescale),
            spec_mean = mean(adcap_spec_rescale),
            spec_sd   = sd(adcap_spec_rescale)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  gather(component1, mean, ends_with('mean')) %>%
  gather(component2, sd, ends_with('sd')) %>%
  filter(str_sub(component1, 1, 4) == str_sub(component2, 1, 4)) %>%
  mutate(component = str_replace(component1, '_mean', '')) %>%
  select(-component1, -component2)
            
ggplot(spp_vuln_summary, aes(x = stressor, color = component, group = component)) +
  ggtheme_plot() +
  geom_point(aes(y = mean), position = position_dodge(width = .8)) +
  geom_linerange(aes(ymin = mean - sd, ymax = mean + sd),
                 position = position_dodge(width = .8)) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = .5),
        strip.background = element_rect(fill = 'grey90')) +
  facet_wrap(~ sheet, scales = 'free_y')

4.2 Question parking lot:

How to score sensitivity traits

  • add up all sensitivity-trait values that are turned on? can be continuous, greater than one
  • how to avoid double counting (e.g.air sea interface and lungs for wildlife strikes?)
  • how to be methodical about scoring sensitivity on a continuous scale?

How to score adaptive capacity/exposure potential traits

  • same concerns as sensitivity
  • can we score adaptive capacity based on broader stressor characteristics, instead of individual stressors?
  • general resilience traits (e.g.reproductive) vs specific resilience traits

What about conditional scoring?

  • e.g.flow chart - if a species is in the epipelagic zone, then check whether its air sea interface, etc.

How to connect sensitivity to adaptive capacity? Ad cap as multiplier, e.g.0-1 to mitigate the sensitivity score?

How to incorporate habitats -
